          "date": "2016-01-20 23:07:38.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-7642 build: Allow Lustre to build in absence of git",
        "message": "LU-7642 build: Allow Lustre to build in absence of git\n\nLustre currently refuses to build if it is not in the presence\nof a git working directory.  Subsequent tarballs generated\nfrom \"make dist\" under a git working directory, on the other\nhand, can build without the presence of a git working directory.\n\nThis patch is a quick hack to allow Lustre to build the _first_\ntime through without a git working directory.  This is especially\nuseful if one wants to grab a Lustre source tree using\n\"git archive --remote\", for instance from inside an automated\nbuild system's scripts.\n\nChange-Id: I8d2579dc7bb322b41b5c93fa61e9d2e07fccdcff\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
